{"type":"message","id":"22b5591a","parentId":"bee03869","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:22:44.897Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户说\"我手理解错了吗 spawn不派生agent吗，我们是想直接派活给agent orchestrator 而不是 派生agent干\"\n\n用户的核心问题：\n1. `sessions_spawn` 是「派生」agent（启动一个新 agent 实例/任务）\n2. 但用户想要的是「派活给 agent-orchestrator」——意思是让 agent-orchestrator 这个**已经存在**的 agent 来执行任务\n3. 这两个是不同的：\n   - `spawn` = 启动新的 agent 来跑任务（agent 完成就消失）\n   - `派活` = 给已存在的 agent 持续发任务（agent 是一直在的，能累积记忆/上下文）\n\n用户希望的是：让 agent-orchestrator 一直存在，main 通过通信给 agent-orchestrator 发任务，agent-orchestrator 收到后处理。\n\n这跟我的理解可能有偏差。让我看 sessions_spawn 和 sessions_send 的差异：\n\n**`sessions_spawn`**: 派生一个隔离的子 agent 来跑任务，subagent 是新创建的，task 完就结束。每次都新起。适合一次性、独立任务。\n\n**`sessions_send`**: 给一个**已经存在**的 session 发消息。如果该 agent 有 active session，就会收到消息并继续工作。\n\n但问题是：\n1. `sessions_send` schema 说 \"Send message to visible session by sessionKey/label, or configured agent by agentId. Thread-scoped chats rejected; target parent channel session. **Creates missing configured-agent main session**; waits for reply when available.\"\n2. 也就是说，`sessions_send(agentId=\"agent-orchestrator\", message=\"...\")` 会**自动创建** agent-orchestrator 的 main session，然后发消息给它\n\n这才是用户想要的「派活」——给 agent-orchestrator 发消息，让它处理（它处理完会回复，session 保持存在，可以继续累积工作）。\n\n而 `sessions_spawn` 是另一种模式：派生一个新 subagent 跑一个独立任务（用完就结束，不持久）。\n\n我应该：\n1. 承认理解错了（用户没明说但我误用了 spawn 概念）\n2. 解释 spawn vs send 的区别\n3. 展示怎么用 sessions_send 派活给 agent-orchestrator\n4. 实际派一个活过去（让 orchestrator 把 searxng skill 推给其他 agent）\n\n让我先看看 agent-orchestrator 的 workspace，确认它的 session 处理模式。\n\n不过我应该:\n1. 先回答用户的疑问\n2. 实际用 `sessions_send` 派一个活\n\n注意：sessions_send \"waits for reply when available\"——这会阻塞。spawn 不阻塞。所以 send 派活更适合「派活给有状态 agent」的场景。\n\n实际上更稳的策略：\n1. 解释清楚 spawn vs send 的区别\n2. 立刻用 sessions_send 派活给 agent-orchestrator 处理 SearXNG 任务\n3. 等回复\n\n让我先看 sessions_send 的 schema 细节。\n\n`sessionKey` | `label` | `agentId`：三种寻址方式之一\n- agentId：按 agent 寻址\n- sessionKey / label：按 session 寻址\n\n如果用 agentId=\"agent-orchestrator\"，系统会自动创建/找 agent-orchestrator 的 main session，发消息给它。\n\n所以正确的做法是：\n```\nsessions_send(\n  agentId=\"agent-orchestrator\",\n  message=\"任务说明\",\n  timeoutSeconds=60  // 等回复超时\n)\n```\n\n然后 agent-orchestrator 收到后，会用它的 main session 来处理，处理完返回结果。\n\n好，承认理解错了，正确使用 send 派活。\n\n但我还要注意：用户说\"派活给 agent-orchestrator\"——具体任务是什么？回到上下文：把 searxng-search skill 推给其他 agent。\n\n我应该：\n1. 直接用 sessions_send 给 agent-orchestrator 发任务\n2. 任务内容：把 searxng-search skill 从 main 的 workspace 推给其他需要的 agent（tts/content/director 等）\n\n让我组织好任务消息。\n\n实际上让我先解释 spawn vs send 区别，然后派活。","thinkingSignature":"9fd1d1d4ccec42f69563b611605949b46ab6cda4632489f34cbbded129b1bb66"},{"type":"text","text":"理解了，我之前确实说岔了。**`spawn` 是派生新 agent 跑独立任务（一次性，用完即焚）**，不是「派活」。要派活给 agent-orchestrator 这种**长期存在的角色**得用 `sessions_send`。\n\n**两者的本质区别：**\n\n| | `sessions_spawn` | `sessions_send` |\n|---|---|---|\n| 含义 | 派生新 subagent | 给已存在的 agent 发消息 |\n| 生命周期 | 任务结束 session 就清 | agent 持续在线，session 累积上下文 |\n| 适用场景 | 临时/独立/重活 | 长期协作/状态保持/对话流 |\n| 阻塞 | 默认不阻塞 | 等回复时阻塞 |\n\n**所以 SearXNG skill 推广这事**，正确做法是：\n\n`main` → `sessions_send(agentId=\"agent-orchestrator\")` → orchestrator 收到后处理 → 推 skill 推完回复\n\n我刚才一上来用 `spawn` 是错的——我理解成\"启动新 agent 干这活\"，但你想要的实际是\"派给已经在线的 orchestrator 干\"。\n\n但这里有个**先决问题**：orchestrator 当前**没有 active session**。我先 `sessions_send(agentId=\"agent-orchestrator\")` 试一下——按 OpenClaw 规则会自动创建它的 main session 然后把消息塞过去。\n\n我直接派了："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c6fo1lk7v9by_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"agentId":"agent-orchestrator","message":"【任务：SearXNG 搜索 skill 推广】\n\n## 背景\nmain 的 workspace（`/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace`）下有一个 `searxng-search` skill，路径：\n- SKILL.md: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/searxng-search/SKILL.md`\n- search.py: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/searxng-search/scripts/search.py`\n\nSearXNG 服务运行在 `http://192.168.31.146:8888`（已修复 JSON 403，可用 `--engines bing,baidu,360search`）。\n\n## 你的任务\n1. **目标 agent**：至少给 director、tts、content 这三个 agent 挂上 searxng-search skill（选品/调研/内容搜索高频场景最需要）\n2. **挂载方式**：把这套 skill 复制到目标 agent 的 `~/.openclaw/workspace-<agentid>/skills/searxng-search/` 目录下\n3. **可选优化**（强烈建议做）：\n   - search.py 里把默认 engines 改成 `bing,baidu,360search`（当前默认走外网引擎全 timeout）\n   - 验证每个目标 agent 调用 `python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace-<id>/skills/searxng-search/scripts/search.py \"测试\" --limit 2` 能搜出结果\n4. **完成后回报**：\n   - 推广了哪几个 agent\n   - 改动点\n   - 每个 agent 验证截图/输出\n\n## 注意\n- 你自己（agent-orchestrator）就是负责 agent 设置的，所以这本来是你的活\n- 不要改 main 自己的 skill，那是 main 自己的工具\n- 不要改其他 agent 之外的东西\n\n开干。完成后回我一条简短报告。","timeoutSeconds":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":85541,"output":1580,"cacheRead":114,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87235,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813308512,"responseId":"067440fdc6f8099807f6b2cbbed3fe89"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7832783","parentId":"22b5591a","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:22:45.855Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c6fo1lk7v9by_1","toolName":"sessions_send","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"runId\": \"19a68499-c8e9-4214-9039-ca02e5216259\",\n  \"status\": \"forbidden\",\n  \"error\": \"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled. Set tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true to allow cross-agent sends.\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:agent-orchestrator:main\"\n}"}],"details":{"runId":"19a68499-c8e9-4214-9039-ca02e5216259","status":"forbidden","error":"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled. Set tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true to allow cross-agent sends.","sessionKey":"agent:agent-orchestrator:main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813365839}}
{"type":"message","id":"04096371","parentId":"d7832783","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:22:55.006Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"新问题！OpenClaw 默认禁用了 agent-to-agent messaging：\n> \"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled. Set tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true to allow cross-agent sends.\"\n\n我需要：\n1. 在 `openclaw.json` 里把 `tools.agentToAgent.enabled` 设为 `true`\n2. 但 `config.patch` 可能也保护了这个字段\n3. 所以可能需要直接改 JSON 文件 + 重启 gateway\n\n让我先查 schema。","thinkingSignature":"eb6f5f0ce333c0f2ee6d70d9c8f1240ba4da63b69be5db585f871d1f05da9d91"},{"type":"text","text":"又踩到一个 OpenClaw 的安全开关：**agent-to-agent 通信默认禁用**。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gyww8lyj2oo7_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"tools.agentToAgent"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gyww8lyj2oo7_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 看 openclaw.json 里 tools 部分结构 ===\"\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\ntools = cfg.get('tools', {})\nprint('tools keys:', list(tools.keys()))\nprint()\nprint('agentToAgent config:', json.dumps(tools.get('agentToAgent', {}), ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":104,"output":266,"cacheRead":87221,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87591,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813365883,"responseId":"067441361de0c274092a1ba06b8129e9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e9a9b20","parentId":"04096371","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:22:56.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gyww8lyj2oo7_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"tools.agentToAgent\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"title\": \"Agent-to-Agent Tool Access\",\n      \"description\": \"Policy for allowing agent-to-agent tool calls and constraining which target agents can be reached. Keep disabled or tightly scoped unless cross-agent orchestration is intentionally enabled.\"\n    },\n    \"reloadKind\": \"none\",\n    \"hint\": {\n      \"label\": \"Agent-to-Agent Tool Access\",\n      \"help\": \"Policy for allowing agent-to-agent tool calls and constraining which target agents can be reached. Keep disabled or tightly scoped unless cross-agent orchestration is intentionally enabled.\",\n      \"tags\": [\n        \"tools\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"hintPath\": \"tools.agentToAgent\",\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"enabled\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.agentToAgent.enabled\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"none\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Enable Agent-to-Agent Tool\",\n          \"help\": \"Enables the agent_to_agent tool surface so one agent can invoke another agent at runtime. Keep off in simple deployments and enable only when orchestration value outweighs complexity.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.agentToAgent.enabled\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"allow\",\n        \"path\": \"tools.agentToAgent.allow\",\n        \"type\": \"array\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"reloadKind\": \"none\",\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Agent-to-Agent Target Allowlist\",\n          \"help\": \"Allowlist of target agent IDs permitted for agent_to_agent calls when orchestration is enabled. Use explicit allowlists to avoid uncontrolled cross-agent call graphs.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"access\",\n            \"tools\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"tools.agentToAgent.allow\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"result":{"path":"tools.agentToAgent","schema":{"type":"object","additionalProperties":false,"title":"Agent-to-Agent Tool Access","description":"Policy for allowing agent-to-agent tool calls and constraining which target agents can be reached. Keep disabled or tightly scoped unless cross-agent orchestration is intentionally enabled."},"reloadKind":"none","hint":{"label":"Agent-to-Agent Tool Access","help":"Policy for allowing agent-to-agent tool calls and constraining which target agents can be reached. Keep disabled or tightly scoped unless cross-agent orchestration is intentionally enabled.","tags":["tools"]},"hintPath":"tools.agentToAgent","children":[{"key":"enabled","path":"tools.agentToAgent.enabled","type":"boolean","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"reloadKind":"none","hint":{"label":"Enable Agent-to-Agent Tool","help":"Enables the agent_to_agent tool surface so one agent can invoke another agent at runtime. Keep off in simple deployments and enable only when orchestration value outweighs complexity.","tags":["tools"]},"hintPath":"tools.agentToAgent.enabled"},{"key":"allow","path":"tools.agentToAgent.allow","type":"array","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"reloadKind":"none","hint":{"label":"Agent-to-Agent Target Allowlist","help":"Allowlist of target agent IDs permitted for agent_to_agent calls when orchestration is enabled. Use explicit allowlists to avoid uncontrolled cross-agent call graphs.","tags":["access","tools"]},"hintPath":"tools.agentToAgent.allow"}]}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813376196}}
