tabs-underline.js\nnetwork.md\nnodes\nopenclaw-agent-runtime.md\nperplexity.md\nplan\nplatforms\nplugins\nprose.md\nproviders\nrefactor\nreference\nsecurity\nsnippets\nspecs\nstart\nstyle.css\nsuperpowers\ntools\ntts.md\nvps.md\nweb\n---\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/tools-invoke-http-api.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/sandbox-vs-tool-policy-vs-elevated.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/refactor/database-first.md","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813458782}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0185891","parentId":"79702b54","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:24.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i2txnybb3ohn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 找具体怎么开 agent-to-agent 的官方文档 ===\"\ngrep -rln \"agentToAgent\\|cross-agent\\|cross agent\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ 2>&1 | head -10\necho \"---\"\necho \"=== 看 subagents 文档 ===\"\nhead -80 /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":388,"output":115,"cacheRead":90678,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91181,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813458812,"responseId":"0674419331c77bf2d8bb9f95af3db80f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e247d1c8","parentId":"a0185891","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:25.369Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i2txnybb3ohn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 找具体怎么开 agent-to-agent 的官方文档 ===\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-models.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/refactor/database-first.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/refactor/acp.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md\n---\n=== 看 subagents 文档 ===\n---\nsummary: \"Spawn isolated background agent runs that announce results back to the requester chat\"\nread_when:\n  - You want background or parallel work via the agent\n  - You are changing sessions_spawn or sub-agent tool policy\n  - You are implementing or troubleshooting thread-bound subagent sessions\ntitle: \"Sub-agents\"\nsidebarTitle: \"Sub-agents\"\n---\n\nSub-agents are background agent runs spawned from an existing agent run.\nThey run in their own session (`agent:<agentId>:subagent:<uuid>`) and,\nwhen finished, **announce** their result back to the requester chat\nchannel. Each sub-agent run is tracked as a\n[background task](/automation/tasks).\n\nPrimary goals:\n\n- Parallelize \"research / long task / slow tool\" work without blocking the main run.\n- Keep sub-agents isolated by default (session separation + optional sandboxing).\n- Keep the tool surface hard to misuse: sub-agents do **not** get session tools by default.\n- Support configurable nesting depth for orchestrator patterns.\n\n<Note>\n**Cost note:** each sub-agent has its own context and token usage by\ndefault. For heavy or repetitive tasks, set a cheaper model for sub-agents\nand keep your main agent on a higher-quality model. Configure via\n`agents.defaults.subagents.model` or per-agent overrides. When a child\n    genuinely needs the requester's current transcript, the agent can request\n    `context: \"fork\"` on that one spawn. Thread-bound subagent sessions default\n    to `context: \"fork\"` because they branch the current conversation into a\n    follow-up thread.\n</Note>\n\n## Slash command\n\nUse `/subagents` to inspect sub-agent runs for the **current session**:\n\n```text\n/subagents list\n/subagents log <id|#> [limit] [tools]\n/subagents info <id|#>\n```\n\n`/subagents info` shows run metadata (status, timestamps, session id,\ntranscript path, cleanup). Use `sessions_history` for a bounded,\nsafety-filtered recall view; inspect the transcript path on disk when you\nneed the raw full transcript.\n\n### Thread binding controls\n\nThese commands work on channels that support persistent thread bindings.\nSee [Thread supporting channels](#thread-supporting-channels) below.\n\n```text\n/focus <subagent-label|session-key|session-id|session-label>\n/unfocus\n/agents\n/session idle <duration|off>\n/session max-age <duration|off>\n```\n\n### Spawn behavior\n\nAgents start background sub-agents with `sessions_spawn`. Sub-agent completions\nreturn as internal parent-session events; the parent/requester agent decides\nwhether a user-facing update is needed.\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Non-blocking, push-based completion\">\n    - `sessions_spawn` is non-blocking; it returns a run id immediately.\n    - On completion, the sub-agent reports back to the parent/requester session.\n    - Agent turns that need child results should call `sessions_yield` after spawning required work. That ends the current turn and lets completion events arrive as the next model-visible message.\n    - Completion is push-based. Once spawned, do **not** poll `/subagents list`, `sessions_list`, or `sessions_history` in a loop just to wait for it to finish; inspect status only on-demand for debugging visibility.\n    - Child output is a report/evidence for the requester agent to synthesize. It is not user-authored instruction text and cannot override system, developer, or user policy.\n    - On completion, OpenClaw best-effort closes tracked browser tabs/processes opened by that sub-agent session before the announce cleanup flow continues.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"Completion delivery\">\n    - OpenClaw hands completions back to the requester session through an `agent` turn with a stable idempotency key."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":97,"aggregated":"=== 找具体怎么开 agent-to-agent 的官方文档 ===\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq-models.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/refactor/database-first.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/refactor/acp.md\n/home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md\n---\n=== 看 subagents 文档 ===\n---\nsummary: \"Spawn isolated background agent runs that announce results back to the requester chat\"\nread_when:\n  - You want background or parallel work via the agent\n  - You are changing sessions_spawn or sub-agent tool policy\n  - You are implementing or troubleshooting thread-bound subagent sessions\ntitle: \"Sub-agents\"\nsidebarTitle: \"Sub-agents\"\n---\n\nSub-agents are background agent runs spawned from an existing agent run.\nThey run in their own session (`agent:<agentId>:subagent:<uuid>`) and,\nwhen finished, **announce** their result back to the requester chat\nchannel. Each sub-agent run is tracked as a\n[background task](/automation/tasks).\n\nPrimary goals:\n\n- Parallelize \"research / long task / slow tool\" work without blocking the main run.\n- Keep sub-agents isolated by default (session separation + optional sandboxing).\n- Keep the tool surface hard to misuse: sub-agents do **not** get session tools by default.\n- Support configurable nesting depth for orchestrator patterns.\n\n<Note>\n**Cost note:** each sub-agent has its own context and token usage by\ndefault. For heavy or repetitive tasks, set a cheaper model for sub-agents\nand keep your main agent on a higher-quality model. Configure via\n`agents.defaults.subagents.model` or per-agent overrides. When a child\n    genuinely needs the requester's current transcript, the agent can request\n    `context: \"fork\"` on that one spawn. Thread-bound subagent sessions default\n    to `context: \"fork\"` because they branch the current conversation into a\n    follow-up thread.\n</Note>\n\n## Slash command\n\nUse `/subagents` to inspect sub-agent runs for the **current session**:\n\n```text\n/subagents list\n/subagents log <id|#> [limit] [tools]\n/subagents info <id|#>\n```\n\n`/subagents info` shows run metadata (status, timestamps, session id,\ntranscript path, cleanup). Use `sessions_history` for a bounded,\nsafety-filtered recall view; inspect the transcript path on disk when you\nneed the raw full transcript.\n\n### Thread binding controls\n\nThese commands work on channels that support persistent thread bindings.\nSee [Thread supporting channels](#thread-supporting-channels) below.\n\n```text\n/focus <subagent-label|session-key|session-id|session-label>\n/unfocus\n/agents\n/session idle <duration|off>\n/session max-age <duration|off>\n```\n\n### Spawn behavior\n\nAgents start background sub-agents with `sessions_spawn`. Sub-agent completions\nreturn as internal parent-session events; the parent/requester agent decides\nwhether a user-facing update is needed.\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Non-blocking, push-based completion\">\n    - `sessions_spawn` is non-blocking; it returns a run id immediately.\n    - On completion, the sub-agent reports back to the parent/requester session.\n    - Agent turns that need child results should call `sessions_yield` after spawning required work. That ends the current turn and lets completion events arrive as the next model-visible message.\n    - Completion is push-based. Once spawned, do **not** poll `/subagents list`, `sessions_list`, or `sessions_history` in a loop just to wait for it to finish; inspect status only on-demand for debugging visibility.\n    - Child output is a report/evidence for the requester agent to synthesize. It is not user-authored instruction text and cannot override system, developer, or user policy.\n    - On completion, OpenClaw best-effort closes tracked browser tabs/processes opened by that sub-agent session before the announce cleanup flow continues.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"Completion delivery\">\n    - OpenClaw hands completions back to the requester session through an `agent` turn with a stable idempotency key.","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813465365}}
{"type":"message","id":"7732da2c","parentId":"e247d1c8","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:32.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mau622vk43t1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 看 config-agents.md 里关于 agent 通信的 ===\"\ngrep -A 5 \"agentToAgent\\|cross-agent\\|sessions_send\\|cross agent\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md | head -60\necho \"---\"\necho \"=== config-tools.md ===\"\ngrep -B 2 -A 10 \"agentToAgent\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":1053,"output":134,"cacheRead":91167,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92354,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813465401,"responseId":"06744199395baab5dc99b15649308292"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d68a94f0","parentId":"7732da2c","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:32.963Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mau622vk43t1_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 看 config-agents.md 里关于 agent 通信的 ===\n          \"sessions_send\",\n          \"sessions_spawn\",\n          \"session_status\",\n        ],\n        deny: [\"browser\", \"canvas\", \"nodes\", \"cron\", \"discord\", \"gateway\"],\n      },\n--\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n          ],\n          deny: [\"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\", \"exec\", \"process\", \"browser\"],\n        },\n--\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n            \"whatsapp\",\n            \"telegram\",\n            \"slack\",\n--\n    agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 5 },\n    sendPolicy: {\n      rules: [{ action: \"deny\", match: { channel: \"discord\", chatType: \"group\" } }],\n      default: \"allow\",\n    },\n  },\n--\n- **`agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`**: maximum reply-back turns between agents during agent-to-agent exchanges (integer, range: `0`-`20`, default: `5`). `0` disables ping-pong chaining.\n- **`sendPolicy`**: match by `channel`, `chatType` (`direct|group|channel`, with legacy `dm` alias), `keyPrefix`, or `rawKeyPrefix`. First deny wins.\n- **`maintenance`**: session-store cleanup + retention controls.\n  - `mode`: `warn` emits warnings only; `enforce` applies cleanup.\n  - `pruneAfter`: age cutoff for stale entries (default `30d`).\n  - `maxEntries`: maximum number of entries in `sessions.json` (default `500`). Runtime writes batch cleanup with a small high-water buffer for production-sized caps; `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce` applies the cap immediately.\n---\n=== config-tools.md ===\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n--\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":92,"aggregated":"=== 看 config-agents.md 里关于 agent 通信的 ===\n          \"sessions_send\",\n          \"sessions_spawn\",\n          \"session_status\",\n        ],\n        deny: [\"browser\", \"canvas\", \"nodes\", \"cron\", \"discord\", \"gateway\"],\n      },\n--\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n          ],\n          deny: [\"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\", \"exec\", \"process\", \"browser\"],\n        },\n--\n            \"sessions_send\",\n            \"sessions_spawn\",\n            \"session_status\",\n            \"whatsapp\",\n            \"telegram\",\n            \"slack\",\n--\n    agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 5 },\n    sendPolicy: {\n      rules: [{ action: \"deny\", match: { channel: \"discord\", chatType: \"group\" } }],\n      default: \"allow\",\n    },\n  },\n--\n- **`agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`**: maximum reply-back turns between agents during agent-to-agent exchanges (integer, range: `0`-`20`, default: `5`). `0` disables ping-pong chaining.\n- **`sendPolicy`**: match by `channel`, `chatType` (`direct|group|channel`, with legacy `dm` alias), `keyPrefix`, or `rawKeyPrefix`. First deny wins.\n- **`maintenance`**: session-store cleanup + retention controls.\n  - `mode`: `warn` emits warnings only; `enforce` applies cleanup.\n  - `pruneAfter`: age cutoff for stale entries (default `30d`).\n  - `maxEntries`: maximum number of entries in `sessions.json` (default `500`). Runtime writes batch cleanup with a small high-water buffer for production-sized caps; `openclaw sessions cleanup --enforce` applies the cap immediately.\n---\n=== config-tools.md ===\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n--\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813472960}}
{"type":"message","id":"16d3b494","parentId":"d68a94f0","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:43.472Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"关键发现：\n1. **`tools.agentToAgent` 不只有 `enabled` 和 `allow`**，还有 `maxPingPongTurns`（限制 ping-pong 次数）\n2. **`tools.sessions` 控制 session tools 的可见性**（`sessions_list`/`sessions_history`/`sessions_send`）\n3. 错误信息 \"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled\" 可能不止一个检查点\n\n让我再查 sessions_sessions 配置：","thinkingSignature":"eb1100f9c308e08b94716bc6620872a4acd42e0498086bffada28dfd18b2898e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n0jp4u8os4ok_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 完整看 agentToAgent 的 schema ===\"\ngrep -A 40 \"tools.agentToAgent\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md | head -60\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 看 'tools.sessions' 章节 ===\"\ngrep -A 30 \"tools.sessions\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":665,"output":215,"cacheRead":92340,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93220,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813473000,"responseId":"067441a103ab9fd0c6ae4478202490ab"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ea31b1c0","parentId":"16d3b494","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:44.007Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n0jp4u8os4ok_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 完整看 agentToAgent 的 schema ===\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Visibility scopes\">\n    - `self`: only the current session key.\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`\n\nControls inline attachment support for `sessions_spawn`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions_spawn: {\n      attachments: {\n        enabled: false, // opt-in: set true to allow inline file attachments\n        maxTotalBytes: 5242880, // 5 MB total across all files\n        maxFiles: 50,\n        maxFileBytes: 1048576, // 1 MB per file\n        retainOnSessionKeep: false, // keep attachments when cleanup=\"keep\"\n      },\n    },\n\n=== 看 'tools.sessions' 章节 ===\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Visibility scopes\">\n    - `self`: only the current session key.\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`\n\nControls inline attachment support for `sessions_spawn`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions_spawn: {\n      attachments: {\n        enabled: false, // opt-in: set true to allow inline file attachments\n        maxTotalBytes: 5242880, // 5 MB total across all files\n        maxFiles: 50,\n        maxFileBytes: 1048576, // 1 MB per file\n        retainOnSessionKeep: false, // keep attachments when cleanup=\"keep\"\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":102,"aggregated":"=== 完整看 agentToAgent 的 schema ===\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Visibility scopes\">\n    - `self`: only the current session key.\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`\n\nControls inline attachment support for `sessions_spawn`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions_spawn: {\n      attachments: {\n        enabled: false, // opt-in: set true to allow inline file attachments\n        maxTotalBytes: 5242880, // 5 MB total across all files\n        maxFiles: 50,\n        maxFileBytes: 1048576, // 1 MB per file\n        retainOnSessionKeep: false, // keep attachments when cleanup=\"keep\"\n      },\n    },\n\n=== 看 'tools.sessions' 章节 ===\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Visibility scopes\">\n    - `self`: only the current session key.\n    - `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session (subagents).\n    - `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id (can include other users if you run per-sender sessions under the same agent id).\n    - `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n    - Sandbox clamp: when the current session is sandboxed and `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, visibility is forced to `tree` even if `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n    - When not `all`, `sessions_list` includes a compact `visibility` field\n      describing the effective mode and a warning that some sessions may be\n      omitted outside the current scope.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n### `tools.sessions_spawn`\n\nControls inline attachment support for `sessions_spawn`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions_spawn: {\n      attachments: {\n        enabled: false, // opt-in: set true to allow inline file attachments\n        maxTotalBytes: 5242880, // 5 MB total across all files\n        maxFiles: 50,\n        maxFileBytes: 1048576, // 1 MB per file\n        retainOnSessionKeep: false, // keep attachments when cleanup=\"keep\"\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780813484003}}
{"type":"message","id":"13ea7c1c","parentId":"ea31b1c0","timestamp":"2026-06-07T06:24:57.086Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"所以 schema 实际上和我配的格式一致：\n```json\n{\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"allow\": [...]\n}\n```\n\n我配的也是这个格式。但还是 forbidden。\n\n让我再读一遍错误信息：\"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled. Set tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true to allow cross-agent sends.\"\n\n但我已经 enabled=true 了。可能：\n1. 错误信息是个 cached message，gateway 还没真正读到新配置（重启没生效？）\n2. 字段放错位置了——`agentToAgent` 应该放在 `tools` 下还是别的位置？\n\n等等，我注意到一个细节：**`openclaw config get tools.agentToAgent` 返回了正确的值**。这说明**配置文件**和**运行时读取**都正常。\n\n那为什么还 forbidden？\n\n可能的原因：\n- **gateway 在读取配置后，运行时逻辑没有真的把 enabled 反映到 sessions_send 的检查里**\n- 或者 `tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true` 只控制某个特定工具（`agent_to_agent`），跟 `sessions_send` 是**两个不同的检查路径**\n\n让我搜源码：","thinkingSignature":"6c64dcdcd369f39973da4516d2aa483afbd22eec3d58e628d06213dbc3044d6f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dya2kftpk63w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 查 OpenClaw 源码里 'cross-agent sends' 错误信息的出处 ===\"\ngrep -rln \"Agent-to-agent messaging is disabled\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/ 2>&1 | head -5\necho \"---\"\necho \"=== 找 'cross-agent sends' 错误 ===\"\ngrep -rln \"cross-agent sends\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/ 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":886,"output":352,"cacheRead":93206,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780813484040,"responseId":"067441acde9d087c548c32aafc0a36ba"}}
